# initial_program.py

import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    # all grid points
    grid = [(x,y) for x in range(n) for y in range(n)]
    S = []
    # Iterate in a diagonal fashion
    for sum_coords in range(2 * n - 1):
        for x in range(max(0, sum_coords - n + 1), min(n, sum_coords + 1)):
            y = sum_coords - x
            ok = True
            # check collinearity against every pair already in S
            for i in range(len(S)):
                x1,y1 = S[i]
                for j in range(i+1, len(S)):
                    x2,y2 = S[j]
                    # collinear iff (y2-y1)*(x - x1) == (y - y1)*(x2 - x1)
                    if (y2 - y1)*(x - x1) == (y - y1)*(x2 - x1):
                        ok = False
                        break
                if not ok:
                    break
            if ok:
                S.append((x,y))
    return S
# EVOLVE-BLOCK-END
